Real pro&rsquo;s debug with console.log ;-)
So, here is a quick tip, how you can add logging to a JS script, with ZERO dependencies. Just define log as:
const log = (...args) =&gt; console.log('[context]', ...args) To disable logging, change it to:
const log = () =&gt; () or just uncomment it:
const log = (...args) =&gt; () // console.log('[context]', ...args) also you can have log levels like this:
